parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle valve cable can cause unintended acceleration, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The throttle pedal sticks to the floor
the engine idles at high RPM
the vehicle accelerates suddenly
the vehicle accelerates without pressing the gas pedal
the vehicle is unable to stop
the vehicle loses control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the idle speed control valve can cause the engine to idle at high RPM, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The engine idles at high RPM
the vehicle accelerates suddenly
the vehicle is unable to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control system can cause unintended acceleration, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly
the vehicle accelerates without pressing the gas pedal
the vehicle is unable to stop
the vehicle loses control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatbelt can lead to ejection or improper restraint in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The seatbelt buckle fails to latch
the seatbelt buckle unlatches by itself
the seatbelt retractor fails to lock
the seatbelt gets stuck in cold weather
the seatbelt is loose when wearing bulky clothes
the seatbelt motor is faulty
the teeth on the seatbelt motor are chewed up
the seatbelt release button fails to pop back out
the passive restraint system fails to move along the rail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic seatbelt can lead to ejection or improper restraint in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The automatic seatbelt gets stuck in cold weather
the automatic seatbelt motor is faulty
the automatic seatbelt fails to retract
the automatic seatbelt locks up
the automatic seatbelt causes injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatbelt buckle can lead to ejection or improper restraint in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The seatbelt buckle fails to latch
the seatbelt buckle unlatches by itself
the seatbelt release button fails to pop back out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failure can cause a range of issues, including fires, stalling, and loss of critical vehicle functions, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Burning odor
digital dashboard lights going out
wiring catching on fire
alternator fire
ignition switch fire
intermittent stalling
vehicle stalling
steering wheel locking
and vehicle fires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Wiring harness failure can cause electrical fires, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Wiring catching on fire
electrical wiring fire
vehicle fires
and burning odors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Alternator failure can cause electrical system failure, leading to fires, stalling, and loss of critical vehicle functions, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Alternator fire
vehicle fires
and electrical system failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignition switch failure can cause electrical system failure, leading to fires, stalling, and loss of critical vehicle functions, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Ignition switch fire
vehicle fires
and electrical system failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Steering system failure can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Steering wheel locking and vehicle stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS system fails to function
causing the vehicle to come to an abrupt stop
sporadic braking
or failure to stop the vehicle from accelerating backward. In some cases
the brake pedal continues to depress on its own until it comes to a complete stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of brake pads and rotors can cause the vehicle to vibrate or shudder upon braking, leading to reduced braking performance and increased stopping distances, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: Noise from the brakes
vibration or shuddering upon braking
and failure of the brake pads and rotors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brake pedal to continue to depress on its own until it comes to a complete stop, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake pedal continues to depress on its own until it comes to a complete stop
and the vehicle may stall at low or no speed.
